# function used to create the descriptive tables (of t-tests and anova)
test <- function(dt, byvar) {
  # by_var <- enquo(byvar) 
  by_var <- rlang::sym(byvar)
  temp <- dt %>%
    group_by(!!by_var) %>%
    summarize(mean=mean(logRxExp),
              sd=sd(logRxExp),
              N = n())
  varname <- colnames(temp)[1] # mean of logRxExp by groups

  # anova test/t-test
  if (length(table(dt[,byvar])>2)) {
    anv=anova(lm(dt[['logRxExp']] ~ dt[[byvar]]))
    pval <- anv[['Pr(>F)']][1] # extract the p value
  } else {
    ttest=t.test(dt[['logRxExp']] ~ dt[[byvar]])
    pval <- ttest[[3]]
  }
  
  colnames(temp) <- c('var', 'mean', 'sd', 'N')
  temp <- temp %>%
    add_row(var = varname, mean = NA, sd=NA, N=NA, .before = 1) %>%
    mutate(p_val = ifelse(var==varname, pval, NA))
  return (temp)
}

# pick a df and run testing for all categorical variables
test_table <- function(df, adult_only=F) {
  test_tbl <- data.frame()
  varlist <- c('agegrp', 'sex', 'marriage', 'edulvl', 'race','hispyn', 'immigr',
               'povcat', 'rxuselvl', 'usualpl', 'regionmeps', 'instype')
  if (adult_only==T){
    varlist <- append(varlist, c('health', 'anylmt', 'diabeticev', 'likelydepressed'))
  }

  for (var in varlist) {
    temp <- test(df, var)
    test_tbl <- rbind(test_tbl, temp)
  }
  
  # format the table cells
  test_tbl$mean.sd <- paste0(format(round(test_tbl$mean, 2), nsmall = 2),
                     '(', format(round(test_tbl$sd, 2), nsmall = 2),')')
  test_tbl$mean.sd[test_tbl$mean.sd=="  NA(  NA)"] <- NA
  test_tbl$p_value <- format(round(test_tbl$p_val, 3), nsmall = 3)
  test_tbl$p_value[is.na(test_tbl$p_val)]=NA
  test_tbl$p_value[test_tbl$p_val<=0.001 & !is.na(test_tbl$p_val)] <- '<0.001***'
  test_tbl$p_value[test_tbl$p_val<=0.01 & test_tbl$p_val>0.001 & !is.na(test_tbl$p_val)] <-
    paste0(test_tbl$p_value[test_tbl$p_val<=0.01 & test_tbl$p_val>0.001 & !is.na(test_tbl$p_val)], "**")
  test_tbl$p_value[test_tbl$p_val<=0.1 & test_tbl$p_val>0.01 & !is.na(test_tbl$p_val)] <-
    paste0(test_tbl$p_value[test_tbl$p_val<=0.1 & test_tbl$p_val>0.01 & !is.na(test_tbl$p_val)], "*")
  return (test_tbl)
}

2) Summary statistics of continuous explanatory variables

summary_tbl <- function (df1, df2, var, varname) {
  s <- cbind(data.frame(tibble(summary(df1[[var]]))),data.frame(tibble(summary(df2[[var]]))))
  rownames(s) <- c('Minimum','1st Qu.', 'Median', 'Mean', '3rd Qu.', 'Maximum')
  colnames(s) <- c(paste0(varname, '_all'),paste0(varname, '_adults'))
  s <- round(s,2)
  return(s)
}

sum_tbl <- cbind(
  summary_tbl(df[df$year>=2018,],

# make the plot of the coefficient
# https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/dotwhisker/vignettes/dotwhisker-vignette.html
# function to create the table for plot
dwplot_tbl <- function(model_id){
  model <- eval(sym(paste0('model', model_id)))
  keep_row <- c('instypeMedicare', "instypePHI", "instypeMedicaid+", "instypeOther", "instypeUninsured")
  keep_column <- c("var","change", "changese")
  # keep_column <- c("var","coef", "se_hc")
  temp=create_output(model) %>%
    filter(var %in% keep_row) %>%
    select(keep_column)
  colnames(temp) <- c("term","estimate", "std.error")
  temp$term <- sub("^instype", "", temp$term)
  temp$model<-paste0('Model', model_id)
  return (temp)
}

tbl <- data.frame()
for (i in c(2,3,4,5,7,8)) {
  temp <- dwplot_tbl(i)
  temp$estimate <- temp$estimate*100
  temp$std.error <- temp$std.error*100
  tbl <- rbind(tbl,temp)
}

# make plot for model 9-10
# Make bar chart of the coefficients
dwplot_tbl <- function(modelname, modeltype) {
  temp <- create_outputyr(modelname)
  keep_var <- c()
  var_list <- c('instypeMedicare', "instypePHI", "instypeMedicaid+", "instypeOther", "instypeUninsured")
  for (var in var_list) {
    var2015 <- paste0('year2015:',var)
    var2016 <- paste0('year2016:',var)
    var2017 <- paste0('year2017:',var)
    keep_var <- append(keep_var, c(var2015, var2016, var2017))
  }
  keep_row <- append(var_list, keep_var)
  keep_column <- c("var","change", "changese", 'p_value')
  temp <- temp[temp$var %in% keep_row,keep_column]
  
  # some formating
  temp <- separate(temp, 'var', c('year', 'term'),':')
  temp$term[is.na(temp$term)] <- temp$year[is.na(temp$term)]
  temp$year[temp$term == temp$year] <- 2018
  temp$year <- sub("^year", "", temp$year)
  temp$term <- sub("^instype", "", temp$term)
  temp['model'] <- paste0(modeltype, temp$year)
  temp['modeltype'] <- modeltype
  colnames(temp)[which(colnames(temp) %in% 'changese')] <- 'std.error'
  colnames(temp)[which(colnames(temp) %in% 'change')] <- 'estimate'
  
  return (temp)
}

tbl <- rbind(dwplot_tbl(model9, 'short'), dwplot_tbl(model10, 'long'))

# https://www.datascienceblog.net/post/data-visualization/barplot/
make_bar <- function (tbl, term) {
  df <- tbl[tbl$term == term, ]
  ggplot(df, aes(x = modeltype, y = estimate, fill = year)) +
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") + 
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = estimate - 1.96 * std.error, ymax = estimate + 1.96 * std.error), width = 0.2, position = position_dodge(0.9)) +
    geom_text(aes(label = p_value), size = 4, 
    position = position_dodge(0.85), vjust = -0.5, angle=0)+theme_bw() +
  xlab("Model type") + ylab(term) +
    # ggtitle("Rx spending premium(%) compared to Medicaid only") +
    ggtitle(term) +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(size=14,margin = margin(t = 10, b = -15), hjust=0.95),
          legend.text = element_text(size=13),
          legend.title = element_text(size=13),
          axis.text = element_text(color="black", size=13)) +
    guides(fill=guide_legend(title="Year"))
}

# make the plots
p1 <-make_bar(tbl, 'Medicare')+rremove('xylab')+rremove('x.text')+rremove('x.ticks')
p2 <-make_bar(tbl, 'PHI')+rremove('xylab')+rremove('x.text')+rremove('x.ticks')
p3 <-make_bar(tbl, 'Medicaid+')+rremove('xylab')
p4 <-make_bar(tbl, 'Other')+rremove('xylab')

ggarrange(p1, p2, p3, p4, ncol = 2, nrow = 2,
          common.legend = TRUE, legend = "bottom")

# get the raw coefficient for the interaction term
# When using multiple years' of data, we do not transfer coefficient to percent change
create_outputyr <- function(model, hc_se = T) {
  s <- data.frame(summary(model)$coefficient)
  colnames(s) <- c("coef", "se", "tval", "pval")
  if (hc_se == T) {
    s['se'] <- sqrt(diag(vcovHC(model,type="HC1")))
  }
  
  s$coeflcl <- s$coef - 1.96*s$se
  s$coefucl <- s$coef + 1.96*s$se

  s$est_ci <- paste0(format(round(s$coef, 2), nsmall = 2),
                     '[', format(round(s$coeflcl, 2), nsmall = 2),
                     ' ',format(round(s$coefucl, 2), nsmall = 2), ']')
  s$est_se <- paste0(format(round(s$coef, 2), nsmall = 2),
                     '(', format(round(s$se, 2), nsmall = 2),')')
  s$p_value <- format(round(s$pval, 3), nsmall = 3)
  s$p_value[s$pval<=0.01] <- '<0.01***'
  s$p_value[s$pval<=0.05 & s$pval>0.01] <-
    paste0(s$p_value[s$pval<=0.05 & s$pval>0.01], "**")
  s$p_value[s$pval<=0.1 & s$pval>0.05] <-
    paste0(s$p_value[s$pval<=0.1 & s$pval>0.05], "*")

  return (s)
}

output9 <- create_outputyr(model9)[, c('est_ci', 'est_se', 'p_value')]
output10 <- create_outputyr(model10)[, c('est_ci', 'est_se', 'p_value')]

output_withyr_raw <-merge(output9,output10,
              by.x=0, by.y=0, all=T, suffixes = c(".9",".10"), sort=F)
keep_var <- c()
var_list <- c('instypeMedicare', "instypePHI", "instypeMedicaid+", "instypeOther", "instypeUninsured")
for (var in var_list) {
  var2015 <- paste0('year2015:',var)
  var2016 <- paste0('year2016:',var)
  var2017 <- paste0('year2017:',var)
  keep_var <- append(keep_var, c(var2015, var2016, var2017))
}

write.xlsx(output_withyr_raw[output_withyr_raw$Row.names %in% keep_var,],
           "model_output_withyr_raw.xlsx", col.names=T, row.names=F, overwrite = TRUE)
